enums.name: Auditing
enums.description:
Auditing option specified per service method
by default all service methods are included
add the auditing option if you want to exclude a method in auditing

values.name: VISIBILITY_PUBLIC
values.description: VISIBILITY_PUBLIC specifies that this service is accessible without authentication

values.name: VISIBILITY_SELF
values.description: VISIBILITY_SELF enable call this endpoint from the authenticated user only

fields.name: page
fields.description:
page is used for pagination, if unset only the first page is returned,
the list response contains then the page number for the next page.
fields.label: optional

fields.name: count
fields.description: count is the number of results returned per page, if not given server side defaults apply
fields.label: optional

fields.name: logical_used_storage
fields.description:
Logical Used Storage

Logical storage space used by volume, given in bytes.

fields.name: physical_used_storage
fields.description:
Physical Used Storage

Physical storage space used by volume excluding parity, given in bytes.

fields.name: compression_ratio
fields.description:
commpression ratio

compression ratio userWritten/physicalCapacity

fields.name: total_compression_ratio
fields.description:
total commpression ratio

compression ratio sum(userWritten) / sum(physical capacity)

fields.name: physical_capacity
fields.description:
PhysicalCapacity

The physical capacity that exists in this volume layer

fields.name: physical_owned_capacity
fields.description:
Physical Owned storage Capacity

The capacity that would be freed when volume is deleted

fields.name: unrecoverable_data_integrity_errors
fields.description:
Unrecoverable Data Integrity Errors

Number of data integrity errors that could no be recovered by the system.

fields.name: recoverable_data_integrity_errors
fields.description:
Recoverable Data Integrity Errors

Number of data integrity errors that were recovered by the system.

fields.name: installed_physical_storage
fields.description:
Installed Physical Storage

All installed SSDs capacities over all servers in cluster, given in bytes.

fields.name: managed_physical_storage
fields.description:
Total Attached Physical Storage

Sum of all managed and healthy SSDs capacities, given in bytes.

fields.name: effective_physical_storage
fields.description:
Effective Physical Storage

Effective Physical storage excluding overhead of OVP and Parity, given in bytes.

fields.name: logical_storage
fields.description:
Logical Storage

Sum of capacities of all allocated volumes, given in bytes.

fields.name: logical_used_storage
fields.description:
Logical Used Storage

Logical storage space used by all volumes (n of LBAs x 4096), given in bytes.

fields.name: physical_used_storage
fields.description:
Physical Used Storage Excluding Parity

Physical storage space occupied by all volumes (data only), given in bytes.

fields.name: physical_used_storage_including_parity
fields.description:
Physical Used Storage

Physical storage space occupied by all data including Parity overhead when EC enabled (physical n*disks/(n*disks -1)), given in bytes.

fields.name: free_physical_storage
fields.description:
Free Physical Storage

Free storage before entering to read-only mode , given in bytes.

fields.name: estimated_free_logical_storage
fields.description:
Estimated Free Logical Storage

Estimated free storage before entering to read-only mode assuming current compression ratio, given in bytes.

fields.name: estimated_logical_storage
fields.description:
Estimated Total Available Logical Storage

Estimate of total available logical storage based on current compression ratio (effective * compression)

fields.name: compression_ratio
fields.description:
commpression ratio

compression ratio logicalUsedStorage/physicalUsedStorage

scalarValueTypes.notes: Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers – if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint32 instead.
Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers – if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint64 instead.
Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int32s.
Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int64s.
Always four bytes. More efficient than uint32 if values are often greater than 2^28.
Always eight bytes. More efficient than uint64 if values are often greater than 2^56.
A string must always contain UTF-8 encoded or 7-bit ASCII text.
May contain any arbitrary sequence of bytes.
